column1: # TITLE: Bumble Bee Disease Seasonal Variation Dataset
# COLLABORATORS: Samantha Alger Alison Brody and Nicholas Gotelli
# We collected samples to assay viruses (DWV and BQCV) and Nosema from around 300 bumblebees of various species from 5 sites at 4 different time points
# VARIABLE DESCRIPTION: One line for each column in the data set stating what it is and what the units of measurement are
# id: Sample lab ID (one number to a sample)
# target_name: Name of the disease (DWV = deformed wing virus; BQCV = black queen cell virus; Nosema = Nosema spp.)
# pathogen_binary: Presence/absence for each disease (0 = absent; 1 = present)
# field_id: ID collected in the field and mapped to a lab ID when moleculary work was done
# host_plant: Common name of plant bee was caught on. (flight means the bee was caught in flight and not on a plant)
# bee_caste: Caste of the bee specimen (Male Worker and Queen)
# sampling_event: Four sameling events from may to september (1 2 3 and 4)
# pathogen_load: Pathogen load (genome copies per/bee for viruses and spores per/bee for Nosema) Values have been shuffled for the purposes of class use.
# DATA TRACK CHANGES LOG (use this section to record any changes to the data set after it is created)
